This game uses opencv, and haar cascade classifiers to detect the face.
Blue rectangle demons fall down and the player MUST AVOID the demons. Two red rectangle demons lurk in the corners, menacingly.
Do not let the blue demons touch your face!
First blue demon falls slowly, making the game start off easier. The demons begin to fall more quickly, increasing difficulty.
Player starts with score of 0: Each demon you avoid is worth 5 points.
"GAME OVER" will display in red on the screen if a demon catches your face!
At any time, press 'q' to quit.


Technical details:
This program uses opencv for face detection, webcam input, general image processing, and to draw rectangles.
Haar cascade classifier is used in particular for face detection, compatible XML file was easy to integrate.
Numpy is used for array operations and calculating differences.
Time library is used for games pace, Random is used randomize demon positions.
Download raw file, save, and hop in your terminal and enter "python mirror.py"
ENJOY!!
